Blackberry season = THIS pistachio bark 😮‍💨

Blackberry and pistachio bark
Serves 6-8
Takes 5 mins
V GF

250g pack blackberries
3 tbsp Tesco Finest pistachio crème
150g white chocolate
small handful pistachios, roughly chopped (optional)

1. Line a small baking tray with baking paper and arrange the blackberries next to one another to make a rectangle.
2. In a small bowl, warm the pistachio crème for 10 secs in the microwave. Drizzle over the blackberries.
3. In another small bowl, melt the white chocolate in 20 secs burst in the microwave until smooth and melted. Drizzle over the blackberries and pistachio crème to cover. Sprinkle over the pistachios if using.
4. Place in the freezer for 4 hours or until completely frozen. Break into shards and enjoy.

Cheesy potato waffle ‘tortilla’
Serves 6
GF

1 tbsp olive oil 
�1 red pepper, chopped�
1 onion, finely sliced
�12 frozen potato waffles
 �10 eggs, whisked�
1 tsp smoked paprika
�70g mature Cheddar, coarsely grated �
50g ham, roughly chopped �
small handful peas

1. Preheat the oven to gas 6, 200°C, fan 180°C.
2. Toast 6 of the potato waffles in a toaster on the highest setting, until lightly toasted.
3. Add the oil to a baking dish (about 20 x 28cm) and scatter over half of the onion and pepper. Top with the 6 toasted potato waffles.
4. Sprinkle over half of the cheese, the remaining onions and pepper, and all of the ham and peas. Top with the remaining 6 potato waffles.
5. Whisk the eggs together with some seasoning and the smoked paprika.
6. Pour over the eggy mix and sprinkle over the remaining cheese.
7.  Bake in the oven for 30-35 mins until golden and puffed up.

Recipe ⬇️

Ingredients:
1 bagel, flavour of your choice and sliced in half 
2 eggs, beaten and seasoned
1 mild cheese slice
3 leaves of butterhead lettuce
3 rashers of smoked streaky bacon
½ an avocado, thinly sliced
2 rounds of red onion
2 slices of tomato
2 hashbrowns

1.	Add hash browns into a preheated oven or airfryer until cooked through and golden, around 20 mins.
2.	In the meantime, pan fry bacon until cooked to desired crispiness.
3.	To construct the sandwich, heat a pan to a low to medium heat and pour in the beaten eggs. Immediately place on the two halves of the bagel face down and continue to heat until the egg is fully cooked. Flip the bagels over and fold the egg into the middle so any overhang covers the bagel.
4.	In layered, add on the cheese, lettuce, bacon, avocado, red onion, tomato and hash brown. Cut the egg attaching the lid of the bagel away from the base and place the lid on top. 
5.	Slice, serve immediately and enjoy!

Summery baked Camembert with our NEW Baking Camembert with Hot Honey Dressing, let’s gooooo 🍑☀️

Hot honey baked Camembert with peaches and thyme
Serves 4
Takes 25 mins

285g pack baking Camembert with hot honey dressing
3 perfectly ripe yellow flesh peaches, diced 
1 tbsp light brown soft sugar 
1 tbsp extra-virgin olive oil
3-4 fresh thyme sprigs, leaves stripped
baguette or crusty bread, to serve

1. Preheat the oven to gas 6, 200°C, fan 180°C. Lightly score the top of the Camembert in a criss-cross pattern and place in the centre of a round baking dish; about 23cm.
2. Arrange the peaches around the Camembert and sprinkle over the sugar.
3. Drizzle the oil over the Camembert and peaches and sprinkle over most of the thyme leaves. Bake in the oven for 15 mins.
4. Remove from the oven and drizzle the sachet of hot honey dressing mostly over the cheese and a little bit on the peaches, then return to the oven for a further 5 mins until the cheese is gooey and melted.
5. Serve with remaining thyme leaves and crusty bread for dipping.

POV: it’s 3pm, the afternoon slump has hit, and you’re tucking into a cuppa and a slice of this lighter chocolate cake…🍫😍

Made with yogurt and topped with a rich dark chocolate glaze, it’s sure to supply you with some afternoon energy!

👩‍🍳Ingredients:

🍫For the cake:
150g self-raising flour
1 tsp baking powder
50g cocoa powder
½ tsp fine sea salt
125g light or dark brown sugar
3 medium eggs
175g Greek-style natural yogurt
125ml vegetable oil, plus extra to grease
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tbsp instant coffee granules, dissolved in 3 tbsp boiling water
🍯For the glaze:
20g butter
1 tbsp clear honey
50g dark chocolate, finely chopped

📝Method:
1. Grease and line a 900g loaf tin and preheat the oven to 180°C.
2. Sift the flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt into a mixing bowl then stir in the brown sugar, breaking up any lumps as you go.
3. In a jug, combine the eggs, yogurt, oil and vanilla then pour this into the dry ingredients, along with the coffee. Stir until you have a smooth batter. Pour into the lined loaf tin and shake to level the top. Bake for 40-50 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 10-15 minutes, then turn out to a wire rack to cool completely.
4. For the glaze, melt the butter and honey in a small pan until bubbling. Remove from the heat, add the chocolate and set aside to melt, stirring until smooth. Spread over the top of the cake (leave to cool and thicken up first if it seems too runny to spread), and leave to set.

✏️Recipe by @SainsburysMag
📷: @antduncanphoto

With a chocolate and weetabix base, and orange filling, they’ll make the perfect packed lunch treat for the whole family...

👩‍🍳Ingredients:
120g wheat biscuits
40g cocoa powder
50g almond butter
80ml maple syrup
Juice and zest of 2 oranges 
40g orange marmalade 
60g melted dark chocolate

📝Method:
1. In a bowl combine your crushed wheat biscuits, cocoa powder and wet ingredients to make your dough.
2. Press into a dish and top with your marmalade, melted dark chocolate and orange zest. 
3. Refrigerate until set, slice and enjoy!

If you’re on the hunt for an easy dessert showstopper this Bank Holiday weekend, these rosé peaches and cream pavlovas are just that…🍑🍦

With homemade pink marbled meringue nests, topped with rosé poached peaches, fresh cream, sweet honey and tarte cherries, they’re the perfect way to wow your guests this weekend!🙌

👩‍🍳Ingredients:
For the meringues:
4 large egg whites
¾ tsp lemon juice
200g caster sugar
For the peaches:
500ml rosé wine
1 tsp vanilla bean paste
150g light brown soft sugar
juice of 1 lemon
6 semi-ripe peaches, halved and stoned

To serve:
250ml double cream
1 tsp vanilla bean paste
1 tbsp clear honey
250g fresh cherries, pitted and halved
Handful of fresh mint leaves (optional)

📝Method:
1. Preheat the oven to 110°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper. Place the egg whites and lemon juice in a bowl and beat until the whites form soft peaks and have doubled in volume. Increase the speed, then begin adding the sugar, a spoonful at a time, whisking well between each addition, until the sugar has dissolved and you have a stiff, glossy meringue.

2. Dollop 8 mounds of the meringue onto the baking tray, shaping into round nests. Bake for 2 hours, then leave to cool for 1 hour in the turned-off oven, with the door slightly ajar.

3. Pour the wine into a saucepan and add the vanilla, sugar, lemon juice and 100ml water. Bring up to a simmer. Lower in the peaches, cut-side up, and poach for 10 minutes, turning halfway. Use a slotted spoon to lift the peaches from the poaching liquid, then cut into wedges. Bubble the poaching liquid until reduced to a syrup (about 10 minutes). Allow to cool slightly before returning the peaches. Set aside to cool until ready to serve.

4. In a bowl, whip the cream, vanilla and honey to just-soft peaks. Add a dollop of cream to each of the meringue nests, then spoon the peaches and some of the syrup on top. Scatter with the cherries and a few mint leaves, if using.

*Drinkaware for the facts.

✏️Recipe by @SainsburysMag
📷: @martinpoolephotography

We’ve seen the warm loaded crisps hype, so it felt only right to give it a go - spoiler alert, it’s a yes from us!🙌

Taste the Difference mature cheddar and spring onion crisps topped with all your charcuterie favourites, they’re about to make the ultimate addition to your Bank Holiday picky bits spread...😍

👩‍🍳Ingredients:
1 150g bag Taste the Difference mature cheddar and spring onion crisps
1⁄2 120g pack prosciutto crudo, roughly torn
1⁄2 180g jar pitted Nocellara olives, drained and halved
1⁄2 160g pack chargrilled artichoke antipasti
1 340g pack Taste the Difference Pugliese burrata and sun-soaked tomatoes 
1 tbsp olive oil
pinch chilli flakes

1. Preheat the oven to 200°C, fan 180°C, gas 6. Arrange the crisps on a large baking tray, then bake in the oven for 5 minutes or until warm. Transfer to a serving platter, then immediately top with the torn prosciutto while the crisps are still warm so that the prosciutto fat melts onto the crisps.
2. Tear over the burrata, then top with the olives, artichoke antipasti and sun-soaked tomatoes. Drizzle over olive oil and finish with a pinch of chilli flakes.

👉Send this to a crisp lover!

Our Community Champions will also be spending 25,000 hours this Christmas carrying out local acts of kindness in their communities. Check out your local store to see how you can help make a difference for families who are struggling in your local community. 

#MakeGoodThingsHappen

We all know you can’t beat a Yorkshire pud, but do they belong on a Christmas Dinner? Our award-winning The Best Beef Dripping Yorkshire puddings might be a little too hard to refuse! It’s an age-old question and we want to settle the #DeliciousDebate today, once and for all. Let us know in the comments below 👇🎄

#ChristmasDayDinner #ChristmasFoodIdeas #yorkshirepuddings

Make Christmas morning magical! From poaching the perfect egg to mixing mimosas, we’ve got you covered. Enjoy an epic festive brunch, completely stress-free. Order everything you need from our Christmas Food To Order service online now

Saving the best till last with @Selasigb’s final recipe - black forest cake 😍 

Packed full of cream and chocolate, topped with cherries and surrounded with chocolate meringues - yes, please!
